<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,386,879]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,458,483]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Belongs to the 
<taxonomicName box="[508,655,459,483]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marmorea">
<emphasis box="[508,655,459,483]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">S. marmorea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group. The pale, ochreous cream or yellowish cream, male forewing (in females with purple-brown apical apex), wide, rather square valva with small, curved apical process together with 10 very large horn-like cornuti in the male genitalia distinguish this species from all other 
<taxonomicName box="[1331,1436,530,555]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1331,1436,530,555]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Stigmella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
